br.ufrj.ct.restauranteuniversitario

Class API

  • java.lang.Object
    • br.ufrj.ct.restauranteuniversitario.API

  • public class API
extends java.lang.Object
    Created by Felipe Podolan Oliveira on 30/07/17. This class is responsible for making the calls to the RU API using the Volley HTTP library. Each method represents a different route of the API and the interfaces allow the callbacks.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static interface  API.TicketAllocatorCallback
      This interface is used for the callback of the route POST queues/:queue_id which allocates a ticket in a queue
      static interface  API.TicketSearcherCallback
      This interface is used for the callback of the route GET queues/:queue_id/tickets/:user_id which searches for a ticket in a queue
      static interface  API.TicketUpdaterCallback
      This interface is used for the callback of the route PUT queues/:queue_id/tickets/:user_id which updates a ticket in a queue
      static interface  API.TokenCheckerCallback
      This interface is used for the callback of the route GET /status/token which checks if the JWT token saved in the device is valid
      static interface  API.TokenGetterCallback
      This interface is used for the callback of the route POST clients/token which asks the API for a new JWT token

      • checkToken

        public static void checkToken(android.content.Context context,
                              API.TokenCheckerCallback callback)
        This method makes a HTTP request to the API to check if the JWT token saved in the device (if there is any) is a valid token. Route: GET /status/token.
        Parameters:
        context - the context of the application
        callback - the TokenCheckerCallback interface that allows other methods to call this method and get its results

      • allocateTicket

        public static void allocateTicket(org.json.JSONObject params,
                                  java.lang.String queueId,
                                  android.content.Context context,
                                  API.TicketAllocatorCallback callback)
        This method makes an HTTP request to the API to allocate a ticket in a queue. Route: POST queues/:queue_id
        Parameters:
        params - the params gotten from the interface to be sent in the body of the request
        queueId - the queue id which the ticket is going to be allocated in
        context - the context of the application
        callback - the TicketAllocatorCallback interface that allows other methods to call this method and get its results

      • searchTicket

        public static void searchTicket(java.lang.String attendance,
                                java.lang.String userId,
                                java.lang.String queueId,
                                android.content.Context context,
                                API.TicketSearcherCallback callback)
        This method makes an HTTP request to the API to search for a ticket in a queue. Route: GET queues/:queue_id/tickets/:user_id
        Parameters:
        attendance - the attendance string is a string that is related to a single queue
        userId - the user id whose ticket is to be searched
        queueId - the queue id where the ticket is allocated
        context - the context of the application
        callback - the TicketSearchCallback interface that allows other methods to call this method and get its results

      • getQueue

        public static void getQueue(android.content.Context context,
                            android.widget.Spinner spinnerAttendance,
                            java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> map,
                            android.widget.LinearLayout layout)
        This method makes an HTTP request to the API to get all the available queues. It is used only by the TicketAllocatorFragment and by the TicketSearcherFragment and it updates the spinner within these fragments, displaying all the available queues. It also maps the queues id's and the displayed queues attendance strings in the spinners. Route: PUT queues/:queue_id/tickets/:user_id
        Parameters:
        context - the context of the application
        spinnerAttendance - the spinner that displays the available queues
        map - the map that maps the available queues with their queue string
        layout - the layout that contains a progress bar within the spinner with the "Loading..." text
